parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience erratic behavior, which can lead to accidents, strand the driver, or cause inconvenience.
symptoms: the vehicle stalls out without cause
and the vehicle is not charging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to not start, which can leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the relay switch can cause the vehicle to discharge, leading to electrical system failure, which can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power.
symptoms: and the vehicle is not charging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries, distractions, and loss of control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The airbag deploys suddenly without any apparent reason
or when the vehicle is stationary; the airbag warning lamp may be illuminated prior to deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbags to Deploy in a Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
even at moderate speeds; passengers may be thrown into the windshield or suffer injuries due to the lack of airbag protection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed airbag deployment can reduce the effectiveness of the airbag system, increasing the risk of injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags deploy with a delay after the crash
